><br>Anzikon<br><br>&quot;our greatest battles are those fought within our mind&quot;<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujaxy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaxy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Owner & Admin<br>Nishnabe'kwe'</span><br>  Posts: 332<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/6/02 12:05:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: going..going...gone</span><hr size=1> *hehe* my husband (Daggy) is waiting in the beta pool for Shadowbane.  He hasn't made it in yet, but hopefully it will be soon!  He's driving me nuts about how much he is looking forward to SB.  It does look great though in many ways.  I like PVP and the way you can design towns and buildings and the importance of guilds and war will be just really interesting to see how it pans out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>but I'm moving this to the OT/OOC forum <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src="http://www.soulcadre.com/chessiepic.jpg"><br>Vah Shir Dah Khura<br><a href="http://www.cosfv.com">Circle of Sisters</link><br><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie">Firiona Vie Message Board</link></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 138<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/6/02 12:35:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: going..going...gone</span><hr size=1> PvP games that allow players the ownership and total political and creational control of entire towns, villages, hamlets, guild houses, castles, mage fortresses, city states and empires....... is what REAL PvP should be about. Hence Shadowbane <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br>Shadowbane seems to be the ultimate PvP game... and it will seriously compete with existing PvP games out there like DAoC. <br><br>I'm sure that SB will be a big hit.... the only thing that concerns me is that SB will be a major major magnet for all the griefers in the world. <br><br>I guess we will find out soon enough.... <br><br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A> at: 2/6/02 12:36:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usliver123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sliver123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/6/02 3:52:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: going..going...gone</span><hr size=1> my concern with shadowbane is that there is little focus on content such as we have in EQ. The rest of it sounded ok but DAOC sounded ok too, and didn't impact on EQ at all. I am not worried about losing too many to shadowbane.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/6/02 5:36:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: going..going...gone</span><hr size=1> Sliver, <br><br>you are correct. <br><br>That's because Shadowbane does not care about fixed content like you see in Everquest. <br><br>Fixed pre-made content is not what Shadowbane is focusing on. <br><br>What SB is geared towards is PvP or Realm-versus-Realm-versus-Realm-versus-Realm system. <br><br>What does this mean? <br><br>It means that the storyline and &quot;content&quot; is provided by the players and the player made empires. <br><br>The players ARE the history! <br><br>The players ARE the content! <br><br>The players ARE the kings, and the kingmakers! <br><br>The players ARE the empire builders! <br><br>Sure, Shadowbane has some background story book content. They have different races, and the history of the races like the Humans, the Shades, the Irikei, the Dwarfs, etc. <br><br>But beyond that, my guess is that much of the &quot;content&quot; that you would want in such a game would be delivered via the PvP engine.... by the very fact that the actions and the conflicts and the imperial wars of thousands of players will make the game DYNAMIC (e.g. EQ Legends anyone?) and thus the dynamics of the game means that the players will write their own history. <br><br>&quot;He who wins the wars, gets to write its history....&quot; <br><br>SB seems to be a mixture of MMORPG and wargame. Just my 2 cents. <br><br>And yes I agree.... it's a totally different game from Everquest. So different that it wont really impact EQ very much. it wont be direct competition to EQ..... it could be *indirect* competition at best. <br><br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A> at: 2/6/02 5:40:54 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usliver123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sliver123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/6/02 7:07:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: going..going...gone</span><hr size=1> /shrug we'll find out when they release it I suppose. Sounds like the Legends server kinda, wonder if they charge 40 a month for SB. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/6/02 7:26:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: going..going...gone</span><hr size=1> initial sales of the game won't ever get off the ground if they are stupid enough to charge $40 per month <br><br>they need to be smart and initially charge around $10-$15 monthly for Shadowbane to ever get going in terms of sales <br><br>the only reason that Verant can get away with charging $40 per month is because Verant already has hundreds of thousands of addicted customers. <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><t